1
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:19,480
Listen,

2
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:22,720
I have an idea.

3
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:23,680
Look at this.

4
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:25,240
It not only solves the food problem,

5
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:25,720
but also,

6
00:00:25,840 --> 00:00:26,320
I can even

7
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:27,280
make this village

8
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:28,720
develop rapidly.

9
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,000
What do you mean?

10
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:32,880
You gave me the inspiration.

11
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,320
This crayfish...

12
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,960
the flavor now has a soul.

13
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:36,640
So,

14
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:37,440
you are

15
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,800
its spokesperson.

16
00:00:40,160 --> 00:00:40,840
Spokesperson?

17
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:42,480
And then,

18
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:43,560
we'll turn it into

19
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:44,880
a brand

20
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:45,880
and promote it.

21
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:46,960
First,

22
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:48,440
we'll use the Wei Kingdom as a base.

23
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:49,720
What we need to do

24
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:52,360
is seize the pain points of the people's tastes,

25
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,640
then form an industrial closed loop,

26
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:56,400
and empower the industry.

27
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:58,560
Then, in all directions—north, south, east, west—

28
00:00:58,560 --> 00:00:59,840
radiate it outwards,

29
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:01,800
push it nationwide,

30
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:04,400
and unify the commercial landscape.

31
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:06,240
We also need to give this brand

32
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:07,760
a louder name.

33
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:08,840
Think about it.

34
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:12,520
This is our Wei Kingdom's silt-clearing divine object.

35
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:15,280
Spicy is the most popular flavor.

36
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:16,760
Let's just call it

37
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,400
Wei Shen Ma.

38
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,320
How about that?

39
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,200
Although I don't understand,

40
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,200
it sounds very impressive.

41
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:25,760
I wish you success.

42
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:32,160
But what good is success?

43
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,120
Our two countries

44
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:36,200
are bound to go to war.

45
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:39,040
Look at them.

46
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,400
Back then, to escape the war,

47
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,040
they came here

48
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:45,720
and built this Shangri-La.

49
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:48,120
Now,

50
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:50,040
it seems they can't escape it.

51
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,400
I don't want to fight.

52
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,760
Who wants to fight?

53
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:57,440
But this kind of thing,

54
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:58,920
is it something a Princess like you

55
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,800
and a Strategist like me can decide?

56
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:05,360
How about this?

57
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:07,800
Let's write down the story of this place.

58
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:09,840
I'll write to my father.

59
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,200
You write to the Lord.

60
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,400
Maybe

61
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:13,880
it can stop the war.

62
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,760
Just like you said,

63
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:17,640
who wants to fight?

64
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:20,320
I think that works.

65
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,120
Eat up.

66
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:22,960
It's getting cold.

67
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:27,400
The Daye Kingdom Princess Consort has arrived!

68
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,600
I,

69
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,560
Princess Consort of Daye Kingdom,

70
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,040
Ao Tian,

71
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:49,960
have come this time

72
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:51,240
to do only three things.

73
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:53,240
One,

74
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:54,840
take back the Princess.

75
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,160
Two,

76
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,080
loot the commoners.

77
00:02:58,880 --> 00:02:59,280
Three,

78
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,160
Reconnaissance behind enemy lines.

79
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,360
This third thing

80
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,440
is a military secret of my Daye Kingdom.

81
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,320
So,

82
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:08,320
this time,

83
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,480
I'll mainly talk about the first two.

84
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:14,200
Hand it over.

85
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:19,440
Delicious.

86
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,360
Peel one for me.

87
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:24,800
It's okay, it's okay.

88
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:25,400
Unruly peasants.

89
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,040
Becoming unruly peasants at such a young age.

90
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,080
Crying just because I snatched a shrimp today?

91
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,560
How will he cope when I burn his house down later?

92
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,200
This guy won't...

93
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,360
Strategist.

94
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:34,960
Strategist.

95
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:37,000
Let's observe the situation first.

96
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:37,800
Calm down, calm down.

97
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:40,880
Princess.

98
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,040
Who brought you here?

99
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:43,880
Him.

100
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:44,880
Reward him.

101
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:46,400
Get lost.

102
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,000
I said go back.

103
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,200
I'm talking about you.

104
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,120
Princess.

105
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:53,920
How about

106
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,680
we go back?

107
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,120
The Lord has prepared the wedding banquet.

108
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:56,680
I...

109
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:57,920
Strategist.

110
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,000
Calm down, calm down.

111
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,120
Calm down, calm down.

112
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:02,680
Who said I want to go back?

113
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,000
I like it here.

114
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:06,880
What a coincidence.

115
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,040
I like it here too.

116
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:09,480
Although my troops

117
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,080
got lost in the heavy fog,

118
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:11,760
but it's fine.

119
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:12,960
We'll do some looting,

120
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,520
and take back everything we like.

121
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,440
Fighting is forbidden in this village.

122
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,640
But this time I support you.

123
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,200
Just this once.

124
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,320
Why are you hitting me?

125
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:23,920
I... I...

126
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,240
What did I do wrong?

127
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:26,720
What's wrong with looting the commoners?

128
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:27,800
You guys be the judge.

129
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,360
Aren't commoners born

130
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,880
just to be looted by us?

131
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,960
What did I, Ao Tian, do wrong?

132
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,360
Mr. Long, don't be angry.

133
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:37,960
My surname isn't Long.

134
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:39,600
I'm just called Ao Tian.

135
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:40,240
Alright.

136
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,040
Mr. Long Ao Tian.

137
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:43,440
Our village's ancestral motto

138
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:44,560
is to take pleasure in helping others.

139
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,800
You want to loot the commoners,

140
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,080
that can be discussed.

141
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:48,600
However,

142
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,800
you have to tell us your difficulties,

143
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,960
so we can explore the options.

144
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,040
I don't have any difficulties.

145
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:57,800
No difficulties?

146
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,640
Why not make one up on the spot?

147
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,520
Otherwise, we can't really let you loot.

148
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:05,960
You are mocking me.

149
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,280
Absolutely no such intention.

150
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,960
If my words just now made you uncomfortable,

151
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:11,200
I apologize to you.

152
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,400
I'm sorry, Mr. Long.

153
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,280
My surname isn't Long.

154
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:22,960
Doesn't your village forbid fighting?

155
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,080
I didn't see anything.

156
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,240
With He Qi standing next to him,

157
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:29,680
he looks much more pleasing to the eye.

158
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:32,600
General Wei Long of the Wei Kingdom.

159
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,680
Princess Consort of the Daye Kingdom.

160
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:35,760
What advice do you have for me?

161
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:37,680
Wei Long, right?

162
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,440
I'll remember you.

163
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:41,560
Just you wait.

164
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,200
My Daye Kingdom's army will arrive soon.

165
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:44,760
When that time comes,

166
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,160
I'll behead you first.

167
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,000
Get some rest, Mr. Long.

168
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,240
I'll say it again, my surname isn't Long!

169
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,800
My surname isn't Long!

170
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,080
What are we going to do?

171
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:04,160
What do you mean, what to do?

172
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,800
Between the two of us, civil and martial,

173
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,000
can't we handle him?

174
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,360
You saw it too.

175
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:10,560
His intelligence has returned to a primitive state.

176
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,440
For a moment,

177
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,920
I don't know how to deal with him.

178
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:15,000
Just target his weakness.

179
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:15,960
But the problem is,

180
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:16,960
he is entirely made of weaknesses.

181
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,560
I don't know which to choose.

182
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,120
Hurry up and choose.

183
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,480
Or you'll lose your wife.

184
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:22,280
Right.

185
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:24,000
I'll go ask Yu Tong.

186
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,160
What time do you think it is?

187
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,120
Asking Yu Tong now?

188
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,680
Her husband is here.

189
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,800
Will she still stand by your side?

190
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,120
The Strategist...

191
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:35,320
always loses when it comes to women.

192
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:39,240
Where are you going?

193
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,480
To cook.

194
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:41,440
Didn't we just finish eating?

195
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:41,880
Brother,

196
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:42,800
you said the wrong thing.

197
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,160
You said the wrong thing again.

198
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,520
Which part?

199
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:47,840
"Or you'll lose your wife."

200
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:49,760
"Find Yu Tong."

201
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,560
Which one was it exactly?

202
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,480
What should I do?

203
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,880
It must be that one.

204
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:02,680
Talk too much and you'll slip up.

205
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:06,520
Yu Tong.

206
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,480
Come home with me.

207
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,480
Although you...

208
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,680
have been cold to me the past few days,

209
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:22,000
you never actually left.

210
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,960
Based on that alone,

211
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,560
I don't believe

212
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,800
that you aren't moved at all.

213
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:33,120
From the day you risked your life to save me,

214
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,040
I was indeed moved.

215
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:40,360
Born into an imperial family,

216
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,720
my father and brother

217
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,800
have always treated me as a pawn.

218
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,680
You are the first person

219
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,400
who truly cares if I live or die.

220
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:53,040
So at that time, I was thinking,

221
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:57,200
if we could stay together forever,

222
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,080
how wonderful that would be.

223
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,240
Then let's stay together forever.

224
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:04,160
Won't you come home with me?

225
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:11,920
If Father gets angry,

226
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,960
war will break out at the border again.

227
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,600
The people will suffer.

228
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,600
As the Strategist of the Wei Kingdom,

229
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,320
can you bear that?

230
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:26,120
What kind of bullshit Strategist am I

231
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,840
if I can't even keep the woman I love?
